"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-27-Delphine-Moulin-discusses-the-Paris-2024-Opening-Ceremony-with-CGTN-1vz5xqWeSnC-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Dan Williams  Copied  The Opening Ceremony of the Paris Olympics promises to be a grandiose event. It will be the first time it hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t been held in a stadium. Instead, planners have spent months organizing a performance on the river Seine.  Other innovations for Paris 24 include a Champions Park that will allow fans the chance to meet athletes and watch the action on a big screen at the foot of the Eiffel Tower.  CGTN\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Dan Williams talked with Delphine Moulin who is the Paris 2024 Director of Celebrations about the ceremony.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"